32—34. tibias, double pipes‚ used as an accompaniment to ckoral odes.

barbiton, a large seven-stringed lyre, such as Alcaeus (see 1. 32. 5) *and other Lesbian poets used as an accompaniment to songs.

The tibiae and barbitos, therefore, are equivalent to lyr-ic poetry of both kinds (cf. Introd. p. xviii). The former are here ascribed to Euterpe, the latter to Polyhymnia, but both are attributed by Hor. to Clio (invoked in 1. 12. 1—2) and to Calliope (invoked in 111. 4. 1-4).
